// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mtKyWV iterated offset squares tiling, 2023 by jt
// based on https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mtKcDK offset squares tiling

// Tiling of randomly (horizontally/vertically) offset squares iterated twice.
// Created simple building-like rectangular structures with interior offset tiling.
// Unstructured outside space is tile with the complementary offset.
// Walls are tiled with dominos. Click mouse to untint high-level areas.

// tags: random, tiling, squares, tesselation, merge, combine, align, domino, adjacent

// Ideas: could tatami-tilings be used to fill blocks?
// https://mathoverflow.net/questions/103165/monomer-dimer-tatami-tilings-need-better-relationships-with-other-math-summary
// https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1570866712000561
// https://www.combinatorics.org/ojs/index.php/eljc/article/view/v16i1r126
// https://www.combinatorics.org/ojs/index.php/eljc/article/view/v18i1p109

